{
  "texts": [
    "This setting typically occurs on two-sided matching platforms, where the platform has a set of suppliers and consumers each of which has a utility associated with the opposite side as well as a utility for the outside option.",
    "The platform offers a set of suppliers to each consumer and a set of consumers to each supplier.",
    "All participants independently select at most one individual from the assortment offered to them.",
    "A supplier-consumer match occurs when both sides select each other.",
    "The selection probabilities are typically determined by well-known choice models."
  ]
}